President Obama released a statement expressing gratitude and appreciation for Senator Tom Harkin's 40 years of service representing the people of Iowa in the United States Congress. Harkin, the longest-serving Democrat in Iowa's history, has been dedicated to improving the lives of Americans with disabilities, reforming education, and ensuring affordable healthcare for all. The President expressed that Senator Harkin will be missed and wished him and his wife, Ruth, the best in their future endeavors.